text:
Recently log traces were added everywhere an exception was silently ignored.  
In this case, I believe the exception is totally expected, and returning null 
was the appropriate behavior, without a warning.

I tried to make this more obvious in my patch than it was before by moving 
the "return null;" statement in the catch block and adding a javadoc comment.
creator: mcormier@miranda.com
